'''Koike Otsuka Kofun''' ({{ill|Koike Otsuka Kofun|ja|小池大塚古墳|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Koike Otsuka Kofun|qq=}}) is an ancient Kofun ([[:en:Kofun|Kofun]]) located in Koike, Shibayama Town, Sanbu District, Chiba Prefecture.

== Overview ==
This tumulus is a keyhole-shaped Kofun ([[:en:Zenpokoenfun|Zenpokoenfun]]) situated on a plateau along the eastern bank of the upper reaches of the {{ill|Kido River (Chiba)|ja|木戸川 (千葉県)|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kido River (Chiba)|qq=}} in the Kujukuri Plain. The mound measures 72 meters in total length, with a posterior circular diameter of 46.5 meters, a frontal length of 35 meters, a frontal width of 51 meters, a constricted width of 43 meters, a posterior height of 5.2 meters, and a frontal height of 5.7 meters. Including the surrounding shield-shaped moat, the overall length extends to approximately 90 meters. The site was excavated by Waseda University's Archaeological Research Laboratory in 1966 and surveyed by the Chiba Prefectural Board of Education in 1988.

The burial facility is a double-sleeved horizontal stone chamber ({{ill|Yokoana-shiki sekishitsu|ja|横穴式石室|1=Corridor-Style Stone Chamber|2=ja|3=横穴式石室|4=zh|5=橫穴式石室|6=ko|7=굴식 돌방무덤|1=Corridor-Style Stone Chamber|2=ja|3=横穴式石室|1=Corridor-Style Stone Chamber|2=ja|3=横穴式石室|4=zh|5=橫穴式石室|6=ko|7=굴식 돌방무덤|4=zh|5=橫穴式石室|6=ko|7=굴식 돌방무덤|1=Corridor-Style Stone Chamber|1=Corridor-Style Stone Chamber|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yokoana-shiki sekishitsu|13=User:Immanuelle/Corridor-Style Stone Chamber|qq=}}) constructed of cut sandstone blocks, with an overall length of 5.25 meters. Although evidence of looting is apparent, artifacts such as straight swords, iron arrowheads, iron nails, glass beads, Sue pottery, and Haji pottery have been recovered. The absence of [[:en:Haniwa|Haniwa]] suggests the tumulus was constructed in the final phase of keyhole-shaped mounds during the late 6th century. Three additional round tumuli ({{ill|Enfun|ja|円墳|1=Round Kofun|1=Round Kofun|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Enfun|13=User:Immanuelle/Round Kofun|qq=|comment=enwiki is a redirect}}) have been identified nearby, collectively referred to as the Koike Kofun Cluster or Funazuka Kofun Cluster. This tumulus is also known as Funazuka No. 2. Additionally, the neighboring [[:en:Shibayama Kofun Cluster|Shibayama Kofun Cluster]] in Yokoshibahikari Town to the south suggests this site was built subsequent to Shibayama’s Tonozuka and Himezuka Tumuli.

